    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-13T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="415"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-13T13:00:00-03:00"
                            >July 13, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 13—12:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. At the request of the Government the All America Cables has disconnected its
                    cable at Montevideo in order to prevent its use by São Paulo authorities in
                    control of the Santos Station.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
